## Self-Review Checklist

Before submitting code, ask yourself:
- [ ] Did I batch database queries efficiently?
- [ ] Are there any `as any` type casts that should be proper interfaces?
- [ ] Did I extract duplicate logic into reusable functions?
- [ ] Are magic numbers/strings defined as named constants?
- [ ] Does this handle edge cases and invalid inputs gracefully?
- [ ] Would this code be easy to test in isolation?
- [ ] Is the business logic clearly separated from data access?
- [ ] Did I check if this project or its libraries already provide this functionality?
- [ ] Prevent Not Invented Here syndrome.